    <article xml:id="worksheet">
        <worksheet xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" margin="1in" bottom="1.25cm" xml:id="activity-tutorial-1">
            <title>Tutorial-1</title>
            <introduction>
                <p>
                    Following exercises are taken from Section 13.1 of the book <em>Abstract Algebra</em> by Dummit and Foote.
                </p>
            </introduction>
        
        
            <page>
                <exercise>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            Show that <m>p(x)=x^3-2x-2</m> is irreducible in <m>\Q[x]</m>. If <m>\theta</m> is a root of this polynomial, compute <m>(1+\theta)(1+\theta+\theta^2)</m>, and <m>(1+\theta)(1+\theta+\theta^2)^{-1}</m> in <m>\Q(\theta)</m>.
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                </exercise>
        
                <exercise>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            Show that <m>x^3+x+1</m> is irreducible over <m>\mathbb{F}_2</m>, and let <m>\theta</m> be its root. Compute the powers of <m>\theta</m> in <m>\mathbb{F}_2(\theta)</m>. Find the degree of the field extension <m>\mathbb{F}_2(\theta)/\mathbb{F}_2</m>.
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                </exercise>

                <exercise>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            Show that if <m>a\in\Q</m> is a root of a monic polynomial in <m>\Z[x]</m>, then <m>a\in\Z</m>.
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                </exercise>

                <exercise>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            Show that <m>x^5-ax-1\in\Z[x]</m> is irreducible for all <m>a\in\Z\setminus\{0,-1,2\}</m>.
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                </exercise>
            </page>
        </worksheet>
        

    </article>
